tember 2019}}</ref>\n\n; Key to the City\n* {{flagdeco|US}}{{flagicon|Iowa}} [[Muscatine, Iowa]], U.S. (26 April 1985)<ref name=\"National Public Radio2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2012/02/14/146888717/iowa-a-top-destination-for-chinas-vice-president/|title=A Familiar Face Back in Iowa: China's Vice President|last=|first=|date=14 February 2012|newspaper=[[NPR]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714065854/https://www.npr.org/2012/02/14/146888717/iowa-a-top-destination-for-chinas-vice-president|archive-date=14 July 2019|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-17022158|title=The early adventures of Xi Jinping|last=Dailey|first=Kate|date=15 February 2012|newspaper=[[BBC News]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331084433/https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-17022158|archive-date=31 March 2019|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagdeco|US}}{{flagdeco|Iowa}} [[Muscatine, Iowa]], U.S. (14 February 2012)<ref name=\"National Public Radio2\" />\n* {{flagdeco|JAM}} [[Montego Bay]], Jamaica (13 February 2009)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://jis.gov.jm/chinese-vp-receives-key-to-the-city-of-montego-bay/|title=Chinese VP Receives Key to the City of Montego Bay|last=|first=|date=15 February 2009|newspaper=Jamaica Information Service|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714065907/https://jis.gov.jm/chinese-vp-receives-key-to-the-city-of-montego-bay/|archive-date=14 July 2019|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagdeco|CRI}}{{flagu|San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica}} (3 June 2013)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://english.cctv.com/2016/04/06/ARTIOaYH7rGq8JoM8ZFDN64C160406.shtml|title=How many Keys to City has Xi Jinping received?|last=Chen|first=Yue|date=6 April 2016|newspaper=[[China Central Television]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507174548/http://english.cctv.com/2016/04/06/ARTIOaYH7rGq8JoM8ZFDN64C160406.shtml|archive-date=7 May 2019|access-date=5 September 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagdeco|MEX}}{{flagu|Mexico City}}, Mexico (5 June 2013)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flagdeco|ARG}}{{flagu|Buenos Aires}}, Argentina (19 July 2014)<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flagdeco|CZE}}{{flagu|Prague}}, Czech Republic (29 March 2016)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flagdeco|ESP}}{{flagicon|City of Madrid}} [[Madrid]], Spain (28 November 2018)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d514d7949544f30457a6333566d54/index.html|title=President Xi receives Golden Key of Madrid, vows to open up doors of communication further|date=28 November 2018|newspaper=[[CGTN]]|accessdate=13 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513085728/https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d514d7949544f30457a6333566d54/index.html|archive-date=13 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{NoteFoot}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Works cited ===\n{{refbegin|40em}}\n* {{Cite book|title=China's Management Revolution: Spirit, Land, Energy|last=Bou\u00e9e|first=Charles-Edouard|publisher=[[Palgrave Macmillan]]|year=2010|isbn=978-0-230-28545-3|location=|pages=|ref=CITEREFBou\u00e9e2010|author-link=Charles-\u00c9douard Bou\u00e9e}}\n* {{cite book|title=China's Emerging Technological Edge: Assessing the Role of High-End Talent|last=Simon|first=Denis Fred|last2=Cong|first2=Cao|year=2009|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|isbn=978-0-521-88513-3|ref=CITEREFSimonCong2009}}\n* {{cite book|title=Chinese Politics in the Era of Xi Jinping: Renaissance, Reform, or Retrogression?|last=Lam|first=Willy|year=2015|publisher=[[Routledge]]|isbn=978-0765642097|location=|pages=|ref=CITEREFLam2015|author-link=Willy Lam}}\n* {{Cite book|title=China's Political System|last=Heilmann|first=Sebastian|publisher=[[Rowman & Littlefield]]|year=2017|isbn=978-1442277342|ref=CITEREFHeilmann2017|author-link=Sebastian Heilmann}}\n* {{Cite book|title=Inside the Mind of Xi Jinping|last=Bougon|first=Fran\u00e7ois|y