ording to the {{PH wikidata|population_as_of}}, it has a population of {{PH wikidata|population_total}} people.{{PH census|current}}\n\nThe municipality was named after [[Governor-General of the Philippines|Spanish governor-general]] [[Pasqual Enrile y Alcedo]].\n\n==Barangays==\n\nEnrile is politically subdivided into 22 [[barangay]]s.\n{{div col}}\n* Alibago\n* Barangay II\n* Barangay IV\n* Batu\n* Divisoria\n* Inga\n* Lanna\n* Lemu Norte\n* Lemu Sur\n* Liwan Norte\n* Liwan Sur\n* Maddarulug Norte\n* Maddarulug Sur\n* Magalalag East\n* Magalalag West (San Nicolas)\n* Marracuru\n* Roma Norte\n* Roma Sur\n* San Antonio\n* San Jose (Barangay III-A)\n* San Roque (Barangay III-B)\n* Villa Maria (Barangay I)\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Philippine Census \n| align= none\n| title= Population census of Enrile\n| 1903 = 5999\n| 1918 = 7237\n| 1939 = 9506\n| 1948 = 11130\n| 1960 = 16095\n| 1970 = 19431\n| 1975 = 20957\n| 1980 = 23403\n| 1990 = 25608\n| 1995 = 28736\n| 2000 = 29062\n| 2007 = 29719\n| 2010 = 32553\n| 2015 = 35834\n| 2020 =\n| 2025 =\n| 2030 =\n| footnote= Source: [[Philippine Statistics Authority]]{{PH census|2015}}{{PH census|2010}}{{PH census|2007}}{{LWUA population data}} \n}}\nIn the {{PH wikidata|population_as_of}}, the population of Enrile, Cagayan, was {{PH wikidata|population_total}} people,{{PH census|current}} with a density of {{convert|{{sigfig|{{PH wikidata|population_total}}/{{PH wikidata|area}}|2}}|PD/km2|disp=or}}.\n\n==Climate==\n{{Weather box\n| location     = Enrile, Cagayan\n| width        = auto\n| metric first = Yes\n| single line  = Yes\n| Jan high C = 25\n| Jan low C  = 21\n| Feb high C = 26\n| Feb low C  = 21\n| Mar high C = 28\n| Mar low C  = 22\n| Apr high C = 31\n| Apr low C  = 23\n| May high C = 32\n| May low C  = 24\n| Jun high C = 31\n| Jun low C  = 25\n| Jul high C = 31\n| Jul low C  = 24\n| Aug high C = 30\n| Aug low C  = 25\n| Sep high C = 30\n| Sep low C  = 24\n| Oct high C = 28\n| Oct low C  = 23\n| Nov high C = 